comment: This is a page from the ancient Chinese dictionary 'Shuowen Jiezi' (說文解字), specifically Volume 3, Part 2 (第三下). The text includes the title, authorship information, and explanations of characters related to '革' (leather/skin). It features both small seal script (古文) and regular script (楷书), along with phonetic annotations (切) and definitions. The content discusses the etymology and usage of characters derived from '革', such as '軒', '韋', '靭', etc., following the structure typical of Xu Shen's work.
